# Accessibility & Responsive

Mobile-first and breakpoint discipline for UI work.

## Reference

- `documentation/RESPONSIVE_DESIGN.md` — breakpoints, patterns

## Rules

- Test layout at mobile + desktop breakpoints when changing shells or sidebars
- Instructor/student mode shells: hamburger, chat list, feature sidebar interactions
- Touch targets and readable contrast for primary actions
- Prefer semantic HTML in `public/pages/` and `public/components/`

## Chat / monitor / documents

- Long content scroll regions; modals keyboard-dismiss where feasible
- Do not break existing responsive sidebar collapse behavior without Architect note

Coordinate with `01-css-master.mdc` for visual changes.
